headline: Micron falls after Edgewater sees softening outlook in 2025
summary: Shares of Micron (MU) are moving lower after Edgewater Research, which focuses on contacts across industries and supply chains, trimmed its NAND and DRAM price forecasts. The firm sees Micron’s outlook softening further in the first half of 2025, contacts tell The Fly. Shares of Micron are down 3%, or $2.85, to $105.80 in premarket trading.
